      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DIAMANTINA ROSE (6) is a speedy mare who just missed fresh and can go one better. Super honest with two wins and eight minors from 11 starts and only unplaced run was a length fifth jumping from an outside gate in a hot form race. Loves the sharp trip and with brilliant speed is the one to run down. MISTER TUDOR (7) has been racing well and looks close to a win. Ran fourth in the same race as the speedy mare last time and looks a leading chance again. JACKA STANDS ALONE (3) returns and goes well fresh. Has a good record here and with strong early speed and the inside gate should be in this for a long way. WATER LAD (8) is having his first run for a new yard and facing the easiest race in a long while. A few starts ago was in open class sprints in NSW. Can find some form for the new yard. DONT CALL ME HONEY (4) goes very well fresh and returns in a winnable race.",
